Shimon Ornest: In our concerts we want to accumulate positive energy
It is said that in less than a month the end of the world will come, what do you think about it?
It’s just one of so many other alarming news that we like to catch.
The Tap Tap music group likes to do jokes about this and we like to say that we are the only music group in the world that manages to gather enough positive energy to postpone the end of the world or to avoid it.
Moreover, in December you will organize a truly original project: three concerts against the end of the world.
Can you explain it to our readers?
This is a state-of-the-art act that we have planned for two years.
We decided to take advantage of the marketing potential that has the end of the Maya calendar enunciated for December 21 at 11:10 a.m.
The previous day, December 20 at 21 hours, we will host 3 simultaneous concerts in Prague, Brno and Ostrava.
They will end approximately at the same hour in which the Mayan calendar ends on the island of Kiribati, in the Pacific Ocean, 12 hours ahead of our time zone.
To whom came this idea?
Initially it was my idea, then we went forging the project all together with our designer Honza Augusta.
In addition to wanting to gather enough positive energy and avoid the end of the world, we also want to reflect, together with society, on the state in which we will leave the world to our children.
On the occasion of the end of the Mayan calendar we have also created a unique collection of items: boots, shirts, bags and original keys against the end of the world that can be acquired at www.e-tap.cz, another way to support us.
The band The Tap Tap, along with other interprets, also sang the so-called himne against the end of the world, which takes the title "End of the world, cancelled".
Currently it’s very popular on YouTube, can you hear it at the beneficial concerts?
Of course, yes, and it will be just the last, well, as long as everything goes well and the world doesn’t end...
The song will be played by all performers at the same time in the three concerts.
The hymns will be linked together simultaneously thanks to the special live broadcast on the Czech Television.
Tomáš Hanák has written the letter of this song and plays the protagonist role of Jesus in the video clip, where he also sings Xindl X...
How did this collaboration arise?
We work together even with other personalities of the Czech cultural scene, in addition to organizing many beneficial events and concerts.
We are committed to participating in this project.
It has been shown that most of them are interested and enjoy working with us.
To what will the money collected in the concerts against the end of the world be destroyed?
To equipment for the educational center without barriers Study, which we take to end in its sixth year in a row with the civil association Tap in Jedličkův ústav.
Students of the Jedličkův ústav school regularly receive the visit of teachers with whom they do fun and interesting activities.
Students do not have sufficient financial means to pay to teachers and we make an effort to do so possible.
In the framework of the completion of the works in Jedličkův ústav, there will be an independent building to which we will move with this project.
There are several groups and interprets at each concert.
What are the selection criteria?
We try to develop a program that is attractive for all generations, including children.
For example, in Prague they will act Chinaski, Support Lesbiens, Illustratosphere with Dan Bárta, The Tap Tap, Marián Bango and Jiří Suchý.
For more detailed information, you can consult www.kpks.cz.
Do you have any other “spectacular” action in the future?
In May we will act for the first time at the Prague Spring Festival, so here we will surely prepare an attractive program with interesting guests.
The next year we would also like to play at the Bohemian National Hall in New York and I personally, taking advantage of that we are in the United States, would like to complete it with performances in Washington and Chicago.
Your plans abroad are not precisely minimalist, so far you have acted for example in Madrid, Brussels, London or Moscow.
The Tap Tap is a group of people with disabilities.
How is the logistics and organization of these trips?
It’s not as difficult as it may seem at first sight.
There are five members in the electric wheelchair, the chairs must travel in the luggage compartment and also we carry a lot of weight, the boxes with the instruments...
ČSA and British Airways were perfectly prepared, which never ceases to surprise me.
Even in Moscow, where we recently returned, everything went out without problems.
Thanks to the exits abroad you can compare the different attitudes of society towards disabled people and other aspects.
What have you met so far?
In Madrid, Luxembourg, London and other cities, everything works better than here; in Russia we have witnessed that, in the east, there is a long way to go.
Unlike Prague, Moscow is full of barriers, there remains unusual that a person moves alone through the city center on an electric wheelchair.
Something as common as it is, for example, giving preference to someone on a wheelchair on an elevator, there is not.
Fortunately, a civil association has been created that strives to thematise the problems of people with disabilities.
In what aspects should we take the example of advanced countries?
There are a lot of things we are going behind...
But it is important to mention that the improvement and improvement of the situation always depends on the people it directly affects.
In London and Madrid it is very normal that people with a serious disability move on their behalf in public and can go to the service, to the museum, wherever they want.
But it’s not very common that a large number of people with disabilities participate in social life actively, in this aspect, with The Tap Tap let’s go a little ahead!
A respectful or barrier-free society is one thing, but when the time comes when eminent athletes, artists, actors, politicians or lawyers arise, it will begin to change everything really.
So far, they are isolated cases of people who have a great force of will.
The Tap Tap group is currently very popular, but if we look a few years ago, what led you to form the group in 1998?
I entered as an educator in Jedličkův ústav, where I had a lot of young people around me who wanted to devote themselves to something.
And since I am a musician, I touch, among others, the saxophone, I founded an amateur group with a working partner.
And over time, as our moderator Láďa Angelovič says, we went a little out of the hands (laughs).
However, popularity has not arrived until these last years, or am I wrong?
It is true that it helped us quite the fact of connecting with famous singers and also working actively to promote the group.
We come to the conclusion that the work that is not seen is as if it did not exist.
Thanks to the aid from the European Union, we can also allow us quality teaching, equipment, etc.
Did you intend to get so far with The Tap Tap?
From the beginning I saw the potential that there was, that something can be done differently.
The world of the show is full of things that look like each other.
It is logical, in its way, everything new is welcomed with caution and takes a long time to accept it.
There are few extraordinary things, but I dare to say that The Tap Tap is one of them.
The impression of someone who sees us for the first time is clearly compassion, it is a natural reaction.
But compassion is completely superfluous because people with disabilities are not abandoned beings who suffer and of whom we should have compassion.
There are people who are able to live a full life and develop, with the condition, of course, that they have the necessary means.
I always say that if something goes well to people with disabilities, then it is not just an advance for them, but for the whole society.
Did it help the fact that you are a demanding boss, as many people describe him?
If we want to do a quality work, we have to be rigorous in many aspects and require a certain discipline.
I think it is completely normal.
Some people come with a romantic vision and with their head in the clouds and when they realize they have to go two days to essay, go to the preparatory test and spend a lot of time traveling and in concerts, the initial euforia quickly leaves them.
But that’s how it works everywhere, in every group that wants to work and get something.
The Tap Tap group currently has twenty members.
How many of them were already at the beginning of 1998?
One is Láďa Angelovič.
We are an open group, people go and go, we cannot avoid it.
Whoever has will and desire will always find the doors open.
