Under the pressure of economic competition, both internationally and within the EU, the government of the Czech Republic will be forced to continue looking for other ways to reduce the social level of the population.
This trend is therefore systematic.
The solution passes through concrete sociopolitical reforms, which strengthen both the participation of state capital and the influence of citizens in the government and weaken the position of monopoly of private capital in society in the benefit of the state.
