In November 1979, a group of Islamist student demonstrations occupied the U.S. Embassy in Tehran and took 52 diplomats as hostages.
His release was to be in exchange for the destroyed shah Mohamed Réza Páhlevi, who after the revolution fled to the U.S., a country that had sponsored his regime for decades.
