The concept is silent.
The roofs are filled.
“There is nothing worse than a half empty library,” says architect Winy Maas.
"I think that thanks to our initiative now all the inhabitants have a certain bond with this building.
Everyone knows that his book is part of the library.
It is only there to decorate.
In this way, the MVRDV study has achieved a whole success in that royal discipline that in the specialized argot is known as "creation of an identity."
The city of Spijkenisse has written a piece of literature history.
No matter how young and unknown it is.
Finally, a starting point to configure your identity.
