And remember that evil is good for those with apocalyptic mentality.
And he’s not the only teacher offering courses on the “end of the world” this semester, in theory the last of history.
At Temple, Deputy Professor Barry Vacker is teaching the course "Media, Culture and the End of the World".
Each week, students explore apocalyptic topics such as nuclear war, zombies, viruses and germs, and global warming.
"We analyze why these ideas proliferate over time," he said, and how they offer hypothetical scenarios that guide certain human behavior.
If the nuclear material falls into the hands of terrorists, for example, it could explode a war.
This month the students analyzed films with apocalyptic topics and explored how they were compared to real-life examples.
“I’ve tried to inform students about what is possible, likely, credible and impossible,” Vacker said.
